        "The voiced phoneme /IY/ shows clear periodic oscillations in the waveform.\n",
        "The repeating pattern indicates regular vocal fold vibration, which is a defining property of voiced sounds.\n",
        "\n",
        "The unvoiced phoneme /SH/ shows no periodic structure.\n",
        "The waveform is irregular and aperiodic, indicating absence of vocal fold vibration.\n",
        "\n",
        "2. Amplitude characteristics\n",
        "\n",
        "The /IY/ waveform has higher amplitude and a smooth energy envelope, reflecting sustained airflow and efficient energy transfer from the vibrating vocal folds.\n",
        "\n",
        "The /SH/ waveform has lower average amplitude with random amplitude fluctuations, caused by turbulent airflow through a narrow constriction.\n",
        "\n",
        "3. Noise-like structure\n",
        "\n",
        "The voiced phoneme /IY/ exhibits a smooth, harmonic waveform with minimal randomness.\n",
        "\n",
        "The unvoiced phoneme /SH/ exhibits a noise-like waveform, characterized by irregular, random fluctuations due to turbulence at the place of articulation.\n"
